bytewm is derived from dwm (suckless.org) ‚ÄĒ the event loop, client
management, tag system, bar layout, and keybinding dispatch are
adapted from dwm's architecture. See LICENSE for details.

KEYBINDINGS
  All use Super (Mod4 / Windows key).

  Super+Return         Toggle scratchpad (dropdown terminal)
  Super+Shift+Return   Open terminal (st)
  Super+p              Open launcher (bytelaunch)
  Super+s              Screenshot (bytesnap)
  Super+c              Color picker (bytepick)

  Super+j / k          Focus next/prev window
  Super+i / d          Increase/decrease master count
  Super+h / l          Shrink/grow master area
  Super+Shift+h / l    Shrink/grow individual client
  Super+z              Zoom (focus master window)
  Super+Left/Right/Up/Down     Move window by 10px (floating layout only)
  Super+Shift+Left/Right/Up/Down  Resize window by 10px (floating layout only)
  Super+Tab            View previous tag
  Super+w              Kill focused window

  Super+t              Tile layout (master-stack)
  Super+b              BSP layout (balanced binary tree)
  Super+m              Monocle layout (fullscreen for all)
  Super+Space          Floating layout (manual positioning)
  Super+Shift+Space    Toggle floating on focused window (per-window)
  Super+f              Toggle fullscreen

  Super+1..5           View tag I..V
  Super+Shift+1..5     Send window to tag I..V
  Super+Ctrl+1..5      Toggle tag visibility
  Super+0              View all tags
  Super+Shift+0        Send window to all tags

  Super+F10            Volume down 5%
  Super+F11            Volume up 5%
  Super+F12            Mute/unmute
  Super+Shift+v        Show volume OSD (bytevol)

  Super+, / .          Previous/next monitor
  Super+Ctrl+L         Lock screen (bytelock)
  Super+Shift+q        Quit (bytewm-exit)

MOUSE
  Super+LeftClick     Move window (tiled ‚Üí floating + move)
  Super+MiddleClick   Zoom
  Super+RightClick    Resize window (tiled ‚Üí floating + resize)
  Super+Scroll        Cycle windows

LAYOUTS
  tile      Master-stack: large master on left, stack on right
  bsp       Balanced binary tree: equally sized grid
  monocle   All windows fullscreen, tab-like switching
  floating  Manual positioning (no auto-tiling)

AUTOSTART
  Place executables in ~/.config/bytewm/autostart.sh
  (e.g. feh --bg-scale ~/wallpaper.jpg, picom &)

STATUS BAR
  Place ~/.config/bytewm/status.sh to show custom status text.
  Output one line to stdout (CPU, RAM, time, etc.).

THEMING
  A full Gruvbox GTK theme is included in themes/bytewm-gruvbox/.
  It is compiled from the Arc theme using the Gruvbox palette.
  Install with:

    mkdir -p ~/.themes
    cp -r themes/bytewm-gruvbox ~/.themes/

  Then enable in ~/.config/gtk-3.0/settings.ini:

    gtk-theme-name=bytewm-gruvbox

  A matching icon theme is available from:
  https://github.com/SylEleuth/gruvbox-plus-icon-pack

  Install with:

    git clone https://github.com/SylEleuth/gruvbox-plus-icon-pack
    cp -r gruvbox-plus-icon-pack/Gruvbox-Plus-Dark ~/.icons/
    scripts/folders-color-chooser -c orange  # folder accent

  Then set in ~/.config/gtk-3.0/settings.ini:

    gtk-icon-theme-name=Gruvbox-Plus-Dark

APPS
  bytewm ships with its own ecosystem of companion utilities:

  bytewdm      Display manager (login greeter). Written in C.
               Supports PAM authentication, user/session selection,
               and starts the X server. Runs as a systemd service.

  bytelaunch   Application launcher. dmenu-style ‚ÄĒ scans $PATH,
               filters as you type, launches on Enter. Written in C.

  bytify       Notification daemon. Reads notifications from
                /tmp/bytify.fifo and draws an OSD overlay. Written in C.

  bytevol      Volume OSD. Shows a volume bar overlay for ~2 seconds.
               Triggered by Super+Shift+v. Written in C.

  bytesnap     Screenshot utility. Captures the root window and saves
                as PPM. Notification via bytify. Triggered by Super+s.
                Written in C.

  bytepick     Color picker. Click any pixel on screen, prints the hex
                color, copies to clipboard via xclip, and shows a popup
                notification via bytify. Triggered by Super+c.
                Written in x86_64 assembly, links libX11.

  bytewm-exit  Logout/restart/shutdown/lock dialog. 4-entry menu
               shown when pressing Super+Shift+q. Written in C.

  bytelock     Screen locker. Gruvbox themed, PAM authentication
                via pam_unix.so. Written entirely in x86_64 assembly,
                links libX11 and libpam.

  bytefetch    System info fetcher (neofetch-like). Written entirely
               in x86_64 assembly, pure syscalls, no libc.

  bytepass     Password generator. Reads /dev/urandom, copies to
               clipboard via xclip. Written entirely in x86_64
               assembly, pure syscalls, no libc.

  bytekill     Process killer. Scans /proc/*/comm, sends signals
               by name or PID. Written entirely in x86_64 assembly,
               pure syscalls, no libc.

FILES
  bytewm.c       Main source
  config.h       Compiled configuration
  config.def.h   Default configuration template
  Makefile       Build system
  apps/          Companion apps:
                    bytelaunch  - dmenu-style app launcher
                    bytesnap    - screenshot utility
                    bytepick    - color picker (x86_64 asm)
                    bytevol     - volume OSD
                    bytify      - notification daemon
                    bytewm-exit - logout/restart/shutdown dialog
                    bytewdm     - display manager (login greeter)
                    bytefetch   - system info (neofetch-like, x86_64 asm)
                    bytepass    - password generator (x86_64 asm)
                    bytelock    - screen locker (x86_64 asm)
                    bytekill    - process killer (x86_64 asm)
   themes/        bytewm-gruvbox GTK theme (Arc-based, Gruvbox colors)
   examples/      Autostart, status script, .desktop file, st theme
